tags: trigger, snare, click
quality_rating:
A snare trigger based on the 6×13″ DW Edge snare.

Not a basic snare. Just a trigger or for effects.

I used ONLY separate mixdown channels on WaveLab Pro 11 for smoother blendfade.

I mildly blended 3 attacks.

The 4 channel is a 60 ㎐ (overdriven 58 ㎐) sinewave in which I applied high and mid cut filters after the initial rendered boost (render it and re-render it/ export it two times).

tags: clap, hand, room, sm57, tiled
quality_rating:
Hand clapped several times in succession then edited into individual hits for programming. The same pair of hands, same place same time. recorded with Sure SM57 microphone placed over conga drum. Ringing can be heard of drum and room. natural sound.

Suggested uses, rotate claps in succession for a feely rhythm or perhaps play two at once or more for effect, de-tune some etc.

Based on my 16x16" Gretsch USA Custom floortom.
